    "en": "Prime Tuples Conjecture",
    "ja": null,
    "latex": "For any `k ≥ 2`, let `a₁,...,aₖ` and `b₁,...,bₖ` be integers with `aᵢ > 0`. Suppose that for\nevery prime `p` there exists an integer `n` such that `p ∤ ∏ i, (aᵢ n + bᵢ)`. Then there exist\ninfinitely many `n` such that `aᵢ n + bᵢ` is prime for all `i`.",
